OL,3,CMore than 25,000 hours lost in one
OL,4,Cmonth due to ambulance handover delays
OL,6,FMore than twenty five thousand hours
OL,7,Fwere lost as a result of ambulance
OL,8,Fhandover delays, as East Midlands
OL,9,FAmbulance Service (EMAS) recorded its
OL,10,Fsecond busiest month on record.
OL,12,FEMAS has apologised to those who have
OL,13,Fexperienced long waits and said teams
OL,14,Fare working tirelessly to improve
OL,15,Fpatient care and staff wellbeing.
OL,17,FThe apology came as the service held
OL,18,Fits first board meeting since a
OL,19,Fcritical incident was declared earlier
OL,20,Fthis month - The first to be put in
OL,21,Fplace in the history of the service.
