OL,3,CMore than 25,000 hours lost in one
OL,4,Cmonth due to ambulance handover delays
OL,6,FThe latest figures show that the month
OL,7,Fof December was the second busiest
OL,8,Fmonth ever recorded by the service,
OL,9,Fwith over 93 thousand reported
OL,10,Fincidents.
OL,12,FThe festive period also saw the second
OL,13,Fworst month for hospital handover
OL,14,Fdelays, with 25,400 hours lost. That's
OL,15,Fequivalent to sixty eight 12-hour
OL,16,Fambulance shifts every day.
OL,18,F"It's been extremely challenging",
OL,19,Fsays EMAS Director of Operations, Ben
OL,20,FHoldaway.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/7
