OL,3,CMore than 25,000 hours lost in one
OL,4,Cmonth due to ambulance handover delays
OL,6,F"There is a potential of harm for the
OL,7,Fpatients waiting for a response so
OL,8,Feverything we do is to try and reduce
OL,9,Fthe risk to ensure patients aren't
OL,10,Fcoming to unnecessary harm.
OL,11,FUnfortunately our patients have to
OL,12,Fwait longer than we'd like therefore
OL,13,Fthis is why it's really important we
OL,14,Fwork as a system to put improvements
OL,15,Fin place so we can respond to patients
OL,16,Fquicker."
